    "name": "Connolly Hayes",
    "profile": "Connolly Hayes are a 'new' band, already creating high expectations and excitement within, and beyond, the blues/rock/soul community, largely on the reputations of the principal members. The Frankie Connolly Band merged with Jess Hayes in 2023, to become Connolly Hayes. Connolly Hayes’ comprises Jess Hayes on vocals, Frankie Connolly on lead guitar and vocals, Richard Clarke on guitar and bv's, Beau Barnard on bass, Andy Wilder on drums and Joe Mac on keyboards and bv's. \r\n\r\n\"‘Formed last year, Connolly Hayes brings together the dynamic vocal harmonies and stunning musicanship of Jess Hayes and Frankie Connolly - each a rising star in their own right - supported by a top-class band. Connolly Hayes are the real deal and we are fortunate indeed to be able to enjoy their carefully-curated blend of soulful blues before they depart for the festival circuit and a European tour. \"A warm combination of gritty blues and smooth soul\" UK Blues Awards 2024 UK Emerging Act of The Year nominee.​\"A b",
